ResourceHeader.ResourceName: Ulysses COSPIN/LET Ion and Electron 10-Minute Average Rates Data
ResourceHeader.Description:
This data set contains 10-Minute averages of:
	                (a) spin-integrated fluxes of protons (0.9-1.2, 1.2-3.0, 1.8-3.8, 3.8-8.0 and 8.0-19.0 MeV), alpha particles
					    (1.0-5.0, 1.9-3.7, 3.7-8.4 and 8.4-19.0 MeV/n), Li,Be,B nuclei (1.9-4.9 and 4.9-26 MeV/n),  C,N,O nuclei
						(2.6-7.1 and 7.1-39 MeV/n)MeV/n), Z GE 10 nuclei (3.0-9.0 MeV/n), 10 LE Z LE 20 nuclei (9.0-50 MeV/n) and
						Z GE 20 nuclei (12-75 MeV/n);
					(b)	8-sectored proton fluxes (1.8-3.8 and 3.8-8.0 MeV);
					(c)	count rates of electrons (0.3-1.0 MeV) and D1, D2, D3, D4 and D5 single detector sensors.  The parameter keys in the parameter-level segments below are specifically relevant to the UFA-accessible versions of the data.
ResourceHeader.Acknowledgement: Please acknowlegde the COSPIN PI (R.B. McKibben), the lead LET CoI (R.G. Marsden) and the UDS and/or NSSDC

InformationURL.Name: README file for COSPIN/LET data files
InformationURL.Description:
The README file at the Ulysses Final Archive (UFA) describes the
		   format of the ASCII data files containing 10-minute average ion
		   and electron fluxes and detector count rates for the COSPIN Low
		   Energy Telescope (LET), and caveats for their use.

AccessURL.Name: UlyssesFinal Archive
AccessURL.Description:
Parent directory containing compressed Ulysses COSPIN/LET 10-minute average rates
		   data organised in daily ASCII files ucosletrYYDOY.dat (YY and DOY are the two digit
		   year and the day of year, respectively) grouped together into yearly files
		   (cosletYY.zip, where YY is the two digit year).

Parameter.Name: Time for the record
Parameter.Description:
Time for the record given in year, day of year, hour, min, and seconds.
                    The given time represents the start of the averaging interval.

Parameter.Name: COSPIN/LET 10-Minute Average 0.9-1.2 MeV Proton Spin-Averaged Fluxes (L1)
Parameter.Description: 10-minute average LET spin-averaged proton fluxes between 0.9 and 1.2 MeV
Parameter.Caveats:
Rate channel L1 (which nominally responds to protons in the energy range
                0.9-1.2 MeV) is derived from a single detector measurement, and as such is
                sensitive to penetrating particles which lose part of their energy in the
                detector. The background contribution depends on the energy spectrum of the
                incident particle population, being negligible for (differential) energy
                spectral slopes of -3.5 or steeper, increasing to 80% of the total counts
                for a slope of -1.0 or harder.

Parameter.Name: COSPIN/LET 10-Minute Average 1.2-3.0 MeV Proton Spin-Averaged Fluxes (L2)

Parameter.Caveats:

	            energy response to protons (1.2-3.0 MeV) is approximate.

Parameter.Name: COSPIN/LET 10-Minute Average 8.0-19.0 MeV Proton Spin-Averaged Fluxes (L21)
Parameter.Description: 10-minute average LET spin-averaged proton fluxes between 8.0 and 19.0 MeV
Parameter.Caveats:
Rate channel L21 (which nominally responds to protons in the energy
                range 9-19 MeV) is also sensitive to higher-energy particles which lose
                part of their energy in the telescope structure. As in the case of L1, the
                background contribution depends on the energy spectrum of the incident
                particle population, being negligible for (differential) energy spectral
                slopes of -2.0 or steeper, increasing to 80% of the total counts for a
                slope of +0.75 or harder.

Parameter.Description: 10-minute average LET spin-averaged alpha fluxes between 1.0 and 5.0 MeV/n
Parameter.Caveats:
Rate channel L22 is derived from a single detector measurement, and the nominal
	            energy response to alpha particles (1.0-5.0 MeV/n) is approximate.

Parameter.Name: COSPIN/LET 10-Minute Average 8.4-19.0 MeV/n Alpha Spin-Averaged Fluxes (L25)
Parameter.Description: 10-minute average LET spin-averaged alpha fluxes between 8.4 and 19.0 MeV/n
Parameter.Caveats:
Rate channel L25 (which nominally responds to alpha particles in the energy range
	            8.4-19.0 MeV/n) is also sensitive to higher energy particles that lose part of their
				energy in the telescope structure.  As in the case of L21, the background contribution
				depends on the energy spectrum of the incident particle population (negligible for
				differential energy spectral slopes of -2.0 or steeper).

Parameter.Name: COSPIN/LET 10-Minute Average 1.9-4.9 MeV/n Li, Be and B Spin-Averaged Fluxes (L26)
Parameter.Description: 10-minute average LET spin-averaged Li, Be and B fluxes between 1.9 and 4.9 MeV/n
Parameter.Caveats:
Rate channel L26 suffers from background due to pulse pile-up for proton fluxes in L2
	            greater than 10 protons/cm^2/s/sr/MeV.

Parameter.Name: COSPIN/LET 10-Minute Average 4.9-26.0 MeV/n Li, Be and B Spin-Averaged Fluxes (L27)

Parameter.Caveats:

	            greater than 30 protons/cm^2/s/sr/MeV.
